HEADWORD: Bergomask
<hw>Ber"go*mask</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A rustic dance,
so called in ridicule of the people of Bergamo, in Italy, once noted for
their clownishness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

